I applied for a position at the commissary through Express Employment Professionals in Camp Hill. I was told I would get my schedule before Friday of last week (I had been waiting since Monday of last week), and was supposed to start Monday of this week. Passed the drug test, background check and the security clearance check at the barracks, ALL with flying colors. I made three trips to Camp Hill/Carlisle to get it finalized and took it upon myself (knowing military protocol) to drive to the barracks to do my security clearance paperwork. I'm glad I thought of doing that because "Sarah" and "Dana" at the employment agency did not. If I had been strictly from a civilian family, and had not known to do that, I would have screwed myself out of a job. The employment agency left me hang. I am extremely disappointed (Actually, I'm quite pissed off). I really wanted to work there and was willing to drive from York to do it! My brother, a Sergeant in the Army, was also really excited for me. :( I took the time, gas, and initiative to do everything I needed to do to start work at the barracks, (Really nice people at the visitors gate, btw! :) ) I just don't know what happened. Could someone please contact me so we can figure out where the lines of communication got crossed? Thanks!

Fastnacht Day is an annual Pennsylvania Dutch celebration that falls on Shrove Tuesday, the day before Ash Wednesday. The word translates to "Fast Night" in English. The tradition is to eat the very best foods, which are part of the German tradition, and lots of it, before the Lenten fast. Fastnachts (pronounced fost-nokts in German) are doughnuts.
